Package ru.nsu.fit.tretyakov

Class GraphAdjacencyList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ru.nsu.fit.tretyakov.GraphAdjacencyList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - is the required type of object that will be stored in the Graph
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Graph<T>
    public class GraphAdjacencyList<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Graph<T>
    Adjacency List is one of the useful graph-structures, because this structure allows user easily delete and add edges and vertices. By this implementation graph can be directed / undirected. Edges can also have weight.

    • Constructor Detail

      • GraphAdjacencyList

        public GraphAdjacencyList​(Vertex<T> vertex,
                          boolean isDirected)
        GraphAdjacencyList constructor. Creates HashMap (that is implementing matrix-structure) of a single vertex.
        Parameters:
        vertex - is the initial vertex that will be stored in the Graph.
        isDirected - equals true if user wants to Graph be directed. Otherwise, Graph will be undirected.

      • GraphAdjacencyList

        public GraphAdjacencyList​(java.util.Collection<Vertex<T>> vertexCollection,
                          boolean isDirected)
        Another Graph constructor that creates the Graph from the required collection of vertices.
        Parameters:
        vertexCollection - is the collection of vertex which will be stored in the Graph.
        isDirected - equals true if user wants to Graph be directed. Otherwise, Graph will be undirected.

      • GraphAdjacencyList

        public GraphAdjacencyList​(boolean isDirected)
        Default constructor. Sets the initial state of the Graph. In the beginning number of vertices and edges are both equals to zero.
        Parameters:
        isDirected - is the type of the Graph: directed (only one certain edge will be stored in the matrix) or undirected (edge-in-out and edge-out-in will be stored in the matrix).
